Sentencas: Effects of silicon and aluminum concentrations in Fe-Cr alloys on the formation of oxide scales were examined in H-2-H2O atmosphere for interconnects of solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs).
Titulo: Effects of Si and Al concentrations in Fe-Cr alloy on the formation of oxide scales in H2-H2O

Sentencas: The morphology and oxide scale growth rates were compared between conventional and modified Fe-Cr alloys (Si and Al concentration reduced).
Titulo: Effects of Si and Al concentrations in Fe-Cr alloy on the formation of oxide scales in H2-H2O

Sentencas: The formed oxide scales were characterized by surface and depth profile analyses.
Titulo: Effects of Si and Al concentrations in Fe-Cr alloy on the formation of oxide scales in H2-H2O

Sentencas: Oxide scales were composed of the following oxide phases from surface to inner oxide scale: Mn-Cr-(Fe) spinel, Cr2O3, Si-rich interface, and Al2O3 internal oxide.
Titulo: Effects of Si and Al concentrations in Fe-Cr alloy on the formation of oxide scales in H2-H2O

Sentencas: Although the scale formation mechanism is similar between conventional and modified alloys, the oxide scale growth rates were decreased in the modified Fe-Cr alloy.
Titulo: Effects of Si and Al concentrations in Fe-Cr alloy on the formation of oxide scales in H2-H2O
Effects of Si and Al concentrations in Fe-Cr alloy on the formation of oxide scales in H2-H2O

Sentencas: conductivity of oxidized Fe-Cr alloys was improved in the modified Fe-Cr alloy due to thinner oxide scale thickness and complete Cr2O3 film with less distribution of insulating Si and Al internal oxides.
Titulo: Effects of Si and Al concentrations in Fe-Cr alloy on the formation of oxide scales in H2-H2O
